cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.HC 

This paper presents a method for tailoring a parametric controller for a gait rehabilitation robot based on human ratings. The paper leverages supervised learning concepts to train a reward model from data, which judges the physiology of the gait cycle using sensor measurements provided by the robot. The automatic feedback controller then chooses the input settings of the robot to maximize the reward. This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it deals with a gait rehabilitation robot. It also involves supervised learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) concepts. The paper also discusses the automatic feedback controller, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves human ratings and expertise, which could be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
